  "clinical_criteria": [
    "At least one positive inpatient or outpatient C. diff antigen or toxin test (includes positive tests for strain A, strain B, or strains A and B)",
    "One or more diagnosis codes for C. diff (ICD-9 008.45) with either: (a) 7-90 days exposure to Class 1 or Class 2 antibiotics followed by 1+ days with diagnosis; or (b) 2+ mentions in progress notes of C. diff terms in non-negated context followed by 1+ days with diagnosis",
    "2+ mentions of C. diff in progress notes (non-negative, non-historical context) without laboratory or diagnosis code confirmation",
    "Exclusion: bone marrow cancer diagnosis in 2-year period prior to index date OR 7 days following index date",
    "Exclusion: chemotherapy in 180-day period prior to index date OR 7 days following index date",
    "Controls: exposure to Class 1 or Class 2 antibiotics 7-62 days before hospital admission, with hospitalization, and no chemotherapy/bone marrow cancer",
    "Controls: exposure to Class 1 or Class 2 antibiotics with continuous enrollment for 5+ years following exposure and no mentions of C. diff (ever)",
    "Covariate timeframes: Nursing home status (-90d to index); Diabetes Mellitus (ever); HIV (ever); Cancer (time 0 to index+7d); Transplant medications (time 0 to index+7d); Corticosteroids (-21d to index); Anti-TNF agents (-21d to index); Antibiotic exposure (-62d to -7d); PPI medications outside exclusionary time (-21d to index)",
    "C. diff terms in progress notes: clostridium difficile, c diff, c dif, difficile colitis, diff colitis, dif colitis, difficile diarrhea, diff diarrhea, dif diarrhea, difficile infection, diff infection, dif infection, difficile enteritis, diff enteritis, dif enteritis"
  ],
  "algorithm_summary": "This algorithm identifies C. difficile colitis cases through three pathways: (1) laboratory-confirmed positive C. diff antigen/toxin tests (gold standard); (2) diagnosis code 008.45 combined with either prior Class 1/2 antibiotic exposure (7-90 days) or progress note mentions; (3) 2+ progress note mentions in non-negated context. Cases are excluded if they have bone marrow cancer diagnoses within 2 years prior or 7 days after index date, or chemotherapy within 180 days prior or 7 days after. Controls are selected based on antibiotic exposure with either hospitalization or 5+ years continuous enrollment without C. diff mentions. The index date is the earliest date of qualifying lab, diagnosis, or mention. Multiple covariates are collected including demographics, comorbidities, medication exposures (PPIs, corticosteroids, immunosuppressants), and nursing home status.",
  "analysis_timestamp": "2026-05-02T20:19:58.879171Z"
}